  Locus:
    Page: 315
    Verse: 14
Tags:
  - Meditation
---
Meditation is not a matter of trying to achieve ecstasy, spiritual bliss or
tranquility, nor is it attempting to be a better person. It is simply the
creation of a space in which we are able to expose and undo our neurotic
games, our self-deceptions, our hidden fears and hopes.
